definition: mountain pass/to close/to shut/to turn off/to concern/to involve
to wade/to be involved/to concern/to experience/to enter (classical)

sentences.english: The subject is the person or thing that the sentence is about.
sentences.chinese: 主語是句子所關涉的人或事物，其後加動詞詞組。

sentences.english: Chapter Four is on the sentential devices in the rhetoric of legal English.
sentences.chinese: 本章述及諸多關涉法律英語句子結構的最常見手法。

sentences.english: Ephraim shall say, What have I to do any more with idols?
sentences.chinese: 以法蓮必說，我與偶像還有什麼關涉呢。

sentences.english: And the king said, What have I to do with you, ye sons of Zeruiah?
sentences.chinese: 王說，洗魯雅的兒子，我與你們有何關涉呢。
